# ALX HTML/CSS Advanced Project

## 📋 Project Overview

This project is a continuation of the **HTML, advanced** project, focusing on **CSS styling and visual design**. The goal is to create a fully styled webpage that matches the design specifications provided in Figma.

## 🎯 Objectives

- Apply advanced CSS styling techniques
- Implement responsive design principles
- Match the provided Figma design specifications
- Create a pixel-perfect recreation of the design mockup
- Practice modern CSS layout methods (Flexbox, Grid)
- Optimize for cross-browser compatibility

## 🎨 Design Resources

### Figma Design
- **Design File**: [Page in Figma](figma-link-here)
- **Fig File**: Available for download
- **Images**: Download project images from provided link
- **Access**: "Duplicate to your Drafts" for full design details

### Fonts Required
- **Source Sans Pro**: [Download here](source-sans-pro-link)
- **Spin Cycle OT**: [Download here](spin-cycle-ot-link)

> **Note**: If your system doesn't have these fonts installed, download them from the provided links above.

## 📁 Project Structure

```
css_advanced/
├── README.md
