│   ├── logo.png
│   ├── favicon.ico
│   └── [other-images]
└── fonts/
    ├── source-sans-pro/
    └── spin-cycle-ot/
```

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- **HTML5**: Semantic markup and structure
- **CSS3**: Advanced styling, animations, and layouts
- **Flexbox**: For flexible layouts
- **CSS Grid**: For complex grid layouts
- **Media Queries**: For responsive design

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- Text editor (VS Code, Sublime Text, Atom)
- Git for version control

### Installation

1. **Clone the repository**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/tony555t/alx_html_css.git
   cd alx_html_css/css_advanced
   ```

2. **Download required fonts**
   - Download Source Sans Pro and Spin Cycle OT fonts
   - Install them on your system or place in the `fonts/` directory

3. **Download project images**
   - Download images from the provided link
   - Place them in the `images/` directory

4. **Open in browser**
   ```bash
   open index.html
   # or simply double-click the index.html file
   ```

## 📱 Responsive Design

The website is designed to be fully responsive across different device sizes:
- **Desktop**: 1200px and above
- **Tablet**: 768px - 1199px
- **Mobile**: Below 768px

## 🎯 Key Features

- [ ] Pixel-perfect design implementation
- [ ] Responsive layout for all devices
- [ ] Cross-browser compatibility
- [ ] Optimized images and assets
- [ ] Clean, semantic HTML structure
- [ ] Well-organized CSS with comments
- [ ] Modern CSS techniques and best practices

## 📝 Development Notes

### Figma Design Considerations
- Some values in Figma may be in float - round them as needed
- Pay attention to spacing, typography, and color values
- Ensure all interactive elements match the design specifications

### CSS Best Practices
- Use semantic class names
- Organize CSS properties logically
- Comment complex CSS rules
- Use CSS custom properties (variables) for consistency
- Minimize CSS redundancy

## 🔧 Customization

Feel free to make relevant changes to the HTML code as needed:
- Add appropriate `alt` attributes for images
- Include proper `meta` tags for SEO
- Add favicon and other meta information
- Ensure accessibility standards are met

## 📊 Performance Optimization

- Optimize image sizes and formats
- Minimize CSS and HTML
- Use efficient CSS selectors
- Implement proper caching strategies

## 🧪 Testing Checklist

- [ ] Cross-browser testing (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- [ ] Mobile responsiveness testing
- [ ] Accessibility testing
- [ ] Performance testing
- [ ] HTML validation
- [ ] CSS validation

